data.title: Association of Latino Administrators and Superintendents
data.meta_site_name: Association of Latino Administrators and Superintendents
data.text:
ALAS serves students across America, particularly historically marginalized students with an emphasis on Latino youth. ALAS state affiliates have over 31 million enrolled students nationwide, of which more than 10 million are English Language Learners. Our dedicated members in districts across more than 25 states actively engage in a broad range of programs, such the ALAS Superintendents Leadership Academy, National Principal Leadership Academy, Womenâ€™s Superintendent Policy Leadership Academy, networking groups, affinity committees, annual events, and webinars. These initiatives aim to foster, highlight and scale equitable and transformative leadership practices of promise.

To become a national member, please reach out to your state affiliate (except for OALA). If there is no state affiliate available, you can join us directly below.
